{
  "genre": "blues",
  "mode": "focus",
  "mixStrategy": "This is a slow-burn blues focus track in E at 75 BPM with shuffle feel. Quarter note = 0.800s. The 12-bar blues form (I7=E7, IV7=A7, V7=B7) cycles over ~28.8s, giving us roughly 1.5 cycles in 45s. FREQUENCY SEPARATION: Bass (Electric Bass, MIDI 28-47) owns the sub-bass and bass range (20-300Hz), locking with the kick drum on beats 1 and 3 while walking through chord tones and chromatic approaches. Piano comping (MIDI 52-67) fills the low-mid to mid range (300Hz-2kHz), voicing dominant 7th chords on beats 2 and 4 in a shuffle comp pattern, staying out of the bass and melody ranges. Steel Guitar melody (MIDI 60-76) sits in the high-mid/presence range (1-5kHz), playing languid blues licks with space between phrases \u2014 call-and-response style \u2014 emphasizing chord tones on strong beats and blue notes (Bb/b5) as passing tones. Drums provide the rhythmic skeleton: kick on 1&3, snare on 2&4, with a shuffle hi-hat pattern using triplet subdivisions. RHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Bass and kick lock together on beats 1 and 3. Snare and piano comp lock on beats 2 and 4. Melody floats over the top, breathing in the spaces. ENERGY ARC: We start gentle (0.4) for bars 1-2, build to 0.6 for bars 3-6, reach a plateau of 0.7 for bars 7-12, sustain through the second cycle bars 1-8, then taper to 0.5 for the final bars. Velocities stay in the focus-mode range (45-75 mostly), with melody peaking at 72 on climactic phrases. The overall effect is a warm, steady, hypnotic blues groove that habituates quickly \u2014 perfect for deep focus.",
